@page "/discipline/section4"
@layout Gsystem.Layout.SimpleLayout
<PageTitle>Section 4: Disciplinary Measures</PageTitle>

<div class="discipline-content">
    <div class="content-header">
        <h1>Section 4: Disciplinary Measures</h1>
        <p class="section-subtitle">DepEd School Discipline Rules of Procedure</p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-body">
        <div class="section-card">
            <h2>4.1 Categories of Disciplinary Measures</h2>
            <p>Disciplinary measures shall be categorized according to the severity and nature of violations:</p>
            
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Minor Violations</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Lateness and tardiness</li>
                    <li>Improper uniform or grooming</li>
                    <li>Minor classroom disruptions</li>
                    <li>Incomplete assignments</li>
                </ul>
                <p><strong>Measures:</strong> Verbal warning, written warning, parent conference</p>
            </div>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Moderate Violations</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Repeated minor violations</li>
                    <li>Disrespectful behavior to teachers</li>
                    <li>Cheating or academic dishonesty</li>
                    <li>Minor property damage</li>
                </ul>
                <p><strong>Measures:</strong> Detention, community service, suspension (1-3 days)</p>
            </div>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Major Violations</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Fighting or physical aggression</li>
                    <li>Bullying or harassment</li>
                    <li>Substance abuse</li>
                    <li>Serious property damage</li>
                </ul>
                <p><strong>Measures:</strong> Suspension (3-10 days), parent conference, counseling</p>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>Severe Violations</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Weapons possession</li>
                    <li>Drug trafficking</li>
                    <li>Sexual harassment or assault</li>
                    <li>Threats to school safety</li>
                </ul>
                <p><strong>Measures:</strong> Long-term suspension, expulsion, legal action</p>
            </div>

            <h2>4.2 Progressive Discipline System</h2>
            <p>The school shall implement a progressive discipline system that provides multiple opportunities for correction:</p>
            
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>First Offense</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Verbal warning and counseling</li>
                    <li>Parent notification</li>
                    <li>Behavior contract</li>
                    <li>Monitoring and support</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Second Offense</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Written warning</li>
                    <li>Parent conference</li>
                    <li>Increased monitoring</li>
                    <li>Behavioral intervention plan</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Third Offense</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Short-term suspension</li>
                    <li>Intensive counseling</li>
                    <li>Community service</li>
                    <li>Probationary status</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>4.3 Alternative Disciplinary Measures</h2>
            <p>For certain cases, alternative measures may be more appropriate:</p>
            
            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>Restorative Justice</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Mediation between parties</li>
                    <li>Community service projects</li>
                    <li>Peer mentoring programs</li>
                    <li>Restitution for damages</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>Counseling and Support</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Individual counseling sessions</li>
                    <li>Group therapy programs</li>
                    <li>Family counseling</li>
                    <li>Academic support services</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>4.4 Special Considerations</h2>
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Age-Appropriate Measures</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Elementary students: Focus on teaching and guidance</li>
                    <li>Junior High: Balance of consequences and support</li>
                    <li>Senior High: Preparation for adult responsibilities</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>Students with Special Needs</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Consider individual education plans (IEP)</li>
                    <li>Coordinate with special education teachers</li>
                    <li>Adapt disciplinary measures as needed</li>
                    <li>Ensure appropriate support services</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>4.5 Documentation Requirements</h2>
            <p>All disciplinary measures must be properly documented:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Incident reports with detailed descriptions</li>
                <li>Witness statements and evidence</li>
                <li>Parent notification records</li>
                <li>Follow-up monitoring reports</li>
                <li>Outcome assessments and evaluations</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Record Keeping</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Maintain confidentiality of all records</li>
                    <li>Secure storage of sensitive information</li>
                    <li>Regular review and updating of files</li>
                    <li>Proper disposal of outdated records</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

